io.confluent.ksql.execution.expression.tree

Class VisitParentExpressionVisitor<R,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.confluent.ksql.execution.expression.tree.VisitParentExpressionVisitor<R,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - The type of the result returned by the visitor
    C - The type of the context object passed through calls to visit[NodeType]
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExpressionVisitor<R,C>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AggregateExpressionRewriter, ExpressionEvaluatorParityTest.ColumnReferenceRewriter, QueryExecutionUtil.ColumnReferenceRewriter

    public abstract class VisitParentExpressionVisitor<R,C>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExpressionVisitor<R,C>
    VisitParentExpressionVisitor is meant to be a base class for an ExpressionVisitor implementation that by default, implements each visit[NodeType] call by calling a delegate visit impl for that type's parent. This is useful for implementing visit behaviour that is common to all nodes of a given type. For example, a visitor may be interested in recording the type of any literal, and so can provide an implementation for visitLiteral rather than implementing visitIntegerLiteral, visitBooleanLiteral, and so on.
